Dr '''Andrea Marshall''' is a [[Marine biology|marine biologist]] known for her research into [[manta ray]]s, and a founder of the [[Marine Megafauna Foundation]].<ref name="NatGeo">{{cite web|url=http://www.nationalgeographic.com/explorers/bios/andrea-marshall/|title=Andrea Marshall, Conservation Biologist|work=[[National Geographic Society]]|accessdate=23 December 2014}}</ref> She was the subject of the [[Natural World (TV series)|Natural World]] documentary ''Andrea: Queen of Mantas''.<ref name= "QoM">{{Cite episode |title= Andrea: Queen of Mantas |series= Natural World |serieslink= Natural World (TV series) |url= http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00nx6sb |accessdate= 2014-01-19 |network= [[BBC]] |date= 2009 |season= 2009-2010 |seriesno= |number= 3 |transcript= |transcripturl= }}</ref>
She completed her PhD on manta rays in 2008 and now works at the Manta Ray & Whale Shark Research Center at [[Tofo Beach]], [[Mozambique]], where she also lives.<ref name="MMF">{{cite web|url=http://www.marinemegafauna.org/who-we-are/andrea-marshall/|title=Andrea Marshall|publisher=[[Marine Megafauna Foundation]]|accessdate=23 December 2014}}</ref>
She is credited with the inclusion of manta rays in the [[Convention on International Trade in Endangered Species of Wild Fauna and Flora]] (CITIES).<ref name="NatGeo" /> She gave a [[TED talk]] in 2012<ref name="MMF" /> and was named a [[National Geographic Society|National Geographic]] "Emerging Explorer" in 2013.<ref name="NatGeoEE">{{cite web|url=http://www.nationalgeographic.com/explorers/grants-programs/emerging-explorers/about/|title=Emerging Explorers Program|work=[[National Geographic Society]]|accessdate=23 December 2014}}</ref>
She developed [[Manta Matcher]], an online [[citizen science]] database for identifying individual manta rays from their unique markings.<ref name="MM">{{cite journal|last1=Town|first1=Christopher|last2=Marshall|first2=Andrea|last3=Nutthaporn|first3=Sebastien|title=Manta Matcher: automated photographic identification of manta rays using keypoint features|journal=Ecology and Evolution|date=2013|volume=3|issue=7|pages=1902–1914|doi=10.1002/ECE3.587|pmid=23919138|pmc=3728933}}</ref>
