'''Antevs Glacier''' ({{Coord|67|19|S|66|49|W|display=inline,title}}), also known as '''North Heim Glacier''', is a [[glacier]] on [[Arrowsmith Peninsula]], [[Graham Land]], flowing north between [[Seue Peaks]] and [[Boyle Mountains]] into [[Muller Ice Shelf]], [[Lallemand Fjord]]. It was named by the [[United Kingdom Antarctic Place-Names Committee]] in 1960 after [[Ernst Antevs|Ernst V. Antevs]], American glacial geologist.
